    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Anatomy, ecology, and behavior of a new species of Scleronema Eigenmann, 1917 (Siluriformes: Trichomycteridae) from coastal drainages in the southern Brazilian Atlantic Rainforest, with comments on the monophyly and phylogeny of the genus" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989235>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989237>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989231>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989277>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989265> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989235>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Skull, Weberian capsule, and premaxilla-maxilla-autopalatine complex of Scleronema carijo, new species, LIRP 16931, 30.3 mm SL, paratype (c&s), in dorsal view. Abbreviations: acf = anterior cranial fontanel; ao = antorbital; ap = autopalatine; cmx = coronomaxillar cartilage; eb = epiphyseal bar; eo = epioccipital; fr = frontal; io10–11 = infraorbital laterosensory pores 10 and 11; le = lateral ethmoid; ll1–2 = trunk lateral line pores 1 and 2; llo = lateral line tubular ossicle; me = mesethmoid; mx = maxilla; pcf = posterior cranial fontanel; pmx = premaxilla; po1–2 = postorbital laterosensory pores 1 and 2; pt = pterotic; pte-sc = posttemporo-supracleithrum; so4 = supraorbital laterosensory pore 4; so6 = supraorbital laterosensory pore 6 (epiphyseal); sp+po+ps = complex bone formed by sphenotic, prootic, and pterosphenoid; ss = sesamoid supraorbital (= barbular of de Pinna et al., 2020); su = supraoccipital; wc = Weberian capsule. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7989235/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989237>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Tridimensional model of the skull, Weberian capsule, and right premaxilla-maxilla-autopalatine complex of Scleronema carijo, new species, LIRP 16930, 37.2 mm SL, holotype. A. dorsal view; B. left lateral view; C. ventral view. Shaded region on the left edge of the skull in dorsal view (A) represents the course of the supraorbital, otic, and postotic laterosensory canals. Abbreviations: acf = anterior cranial fontanel; ao = antorbital; ap = autopalatine; bo+ex = complex bone formed by basioccipital plus exoccipital; eb = epiphyseal bar; eo = epioccipital; fr = frontal; le = lateral ethmoid; llo = lateral line ossicle; me = mesethmoid; mx = maxilla; of = orbital foramen; os = orbitosphenoid; pa = parasphenoid; pcf = posterior cranial fontanel; pmx = premaxilla; pt = pterotic; pte-sc = posttemporo-supracleithrum; sp+po+ps = complex bone formed by sphenotic, prootic, and pterosphenoid; ss = sesamoid supraorbital (= barbular of de Pinna et al., 2020); su = supraoccipital; tff = trigeminofacial foramen; vo = vomer; wc = Weberian capsule. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7989237/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989231>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Scleronema carijo, new species, LIRP 16930, 37.2 mm SL, holotype, in left lateral (above) and dorsal view. Scale bar = 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7989231/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989277>
    dc:description "FIGURE 21. Left suspensorium and opercular apparatus of Bullockia maldonadoi, LIRP 5947, 45.8 mm SL (c&s), in left lateral view.Abbreviations: hcj = hyomandibular cartilaginous joint for skull; hj = hyomandibular joint for skull; hpd = hyomandibular posterodorsal process; hy = hyomandibula; iop = interopercle; mp = metapterygoid; odp = opercular dorsal process for insertion of dilatator operculi and levator operculi; op = opercle; pfex1 = first preopercular foramen for exit of the cutaneous nerve branch of the external mandibular branch of the facial nerve; pfex2 = second preopercular foramen for exit of the cutaneous nerve branch of the external mandibular branch of the facial nerve; pop = preopercle; q = quadrate; qac = quadrate articular condyle for anguloarticular. Scale bar= 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7989277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7989265>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Radiographs of the caudal-fin skeleton of Scleronema carijo, new species: A. LIRP 16931, 36.2 mm SL, paratype; B. MNHCI 10220, 39.2 mm SL, paratype. Abbreviations: af = adipose fin; ep = epural; ha+has = complex hypurapophysis composed of hypurapophysis (ha) and secondary hypurapophysis (has); hu3+hu4+hu5 = dorsal complex caudal plate formed by co-ossification of hypurals 3, 4 and 5; ph+hu1+hu2 = ventral complex caudal plate formed by co-ossification of hypurals 1 and 2 and parhypural; pu1+u1 = complex caudal centrum composed of preural centrum 1 and ural centrum 1; pu2 = preural centrum 2; ur = uroneural. Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7989265/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

